doc.after: Prominent examples of legislatures are the Houses of Parliament in London the Congress in Washington D C the Bundestag in Berlin the Duma in Moscow the Parlamento Italiano in Rome and the Assembl e nationale in Paris By the principle of representative government people vote for politicians to carry out their wishes Although countries like Israel Greece Sweden and China are unicameral most countries are bicameral meaning they have two separately appointed legislative houses 107
